title: The Elusive Pimpernel
creator: Baroness Emmuska Orczy (1865-1947)
description: LibriVox recording of The Elusive Pimpernel by Baroness Orczy. Read by Karen Savage. First Published in 1908, The Elusive Pimpernel is the 4th book in the classic adventure series about the Scarlet Pimpernel. (Summary from Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. Download M4B (206MB)
subject: librivox; audiobook; adventure; french revolution; scarlet pimpernel
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: As always Miss Savage is very good reading English and French, so this is a very good audiobook and it is read wonderfully! The story is not as good as the original Scarlet Pimpernel, but it is a nice sequel.
Wow! I can't believe Karan Savage records on a volunteer basis. The quality is better than many professional audio books that I've listened to. Definitely one of my favorites.
